race.description: Lawd Mark Mudford Rural Property Sales Handicap (Bm58)
race.comment: BLACK NATURE (9) was lining up for the third time last start and she opened her account with a determined win over this course and distance. Progressive mare who maps beautifully just off the pace and can get the job done again. TROPIC (2) started at a short quote and led all the way for a comfortable maiden win over 1280m at Gundagai last time out when fresh from a 15-week spell. Kept fresh since that success and the blinkers go on today so another sharp performance looks on the cards. GLOWING RAPIDS (1) was in outstanding form before leading then knocking up in a Wyong Highway over 1100m recently. Will enjoy less pressure up front today and is a great chance to turn things around. BILLABONG ROSE (6) made it two in a row when she charged home to narrowly win a BM50 over 1200m at Parkes last start. Finds a deeper race today but a mare in form is difficult to knock. The sparingly raced OUTLAW ANNIE (10) is on trial at this trip but cannot be taken lightly.
